<section class="page-header">
    <div class="container text-center">
        <h1>About Ayurveda</h1>
        <p>A brief journey into the world's oldest healing system.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="about-content container">
    <div class="history">
        <h2>History of Ayurveda</h2>
        <p>Ayurveda, which literally means "The Science of Life," is the traditional healing modality of the Vedic culture from India. It is said to be 2,000 to 5,000 years old. Ayurveda emphasizes the prevention of disease, the rejuvenation of our body systems, and the extension of life span.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="doshas-intro">
        <h2>The Three Doshas</h2>
        <p>According to Ayurveda, health is a state of vibrant balance in which all layers of one's life are integrated. This balance is governed by three fundamental energies or principles, known as <strong>Doshas</strong>.</p>
        
        <div class="doshas-grid">
            <div class="card bg-vata">
                <h3>Vata</h3>
                <p>The energy of movement. It governs all bodily functions related to motion, including blood circulation, breathing, blinking, and tissue movement.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card bg-pitta">
                <h3>Pitta</h3>
                <p>The energy of digestion and metabolism. It functions in digestion, absorption, assimilation, nutrition, metabolism, and body temperature.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card bg-kapha">
                <h3>Kapha</h3>
                <p>The energy of lubrication and structure. It supplies water for all bodily parts and systems. It lubricates joints, moisturizes the skin, and maintains immunity.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

